Auteur principal : CRIMINISI A, PEREZ P
Année : 2003

Titre : Object Removal by Exemplar-Based Inpainting

But : Removing large objects from digital photographs


Technique / Algo  : 

The approch employs an exemplar based texture synthesis technique modulated by a unified scheme for determining the fill orfer of the target region, fill priority influenced by pixel value of confidence and image isophotes.


REGION FILLING ALGORITHM
-Extract the manually selected initial front
- Repeat until done : 
	-Identify the fill front , exit if null
	- Compute priorities P(p) pour tout les p du contour
	- Trouver le patch de priorité maximale
	- Trouver le patch Sigq qui minimise la distance au patch 		Sigp
	-Copy image data from Sigq to Sigp 
	- Update C(p) pour tout les points du patch Sigp contenu 		dans le mask


Avantage de la méthode / Cas d'utilisation / Limitations : 
Propagating both linear structure and two dimensional texture into the targer region. Outperforms earlier work in terms of both perceptual quality and computational efficiency. 

Investigating extensions for more accurate propagation of curved structures in still photographs and for object removal from video. 


